# Day 3: File Management & Structural Reconstruction 📂

## 🎯 Objective
Mastering the creation, movement, and deletion of files and directories. In a SOC environment, these skills are essential for organizing evidence and managing analysis tools.

## 🛠️ Commands Mastered
| Command | Action | SOC Use Case |
|:--- |:--- |:--- |
| `touch` | Create a file | Creating "canary" files or logs. |
| `mkdir` | Create a folder | Organizing evidence by case number. |
| `cp` | Copy data | Making a working copy of a suspect file. |
| `mv` | Move/Rename | Moving logs to a centralized directory. |
| `rm` | Remove data | Cleaning up temporary analysis tools. |

## 🧪 Practical Lab: Reconstruction Exercise
I practiced building a nested directory structure, moving files between branches, and then deleting and reconstructing the entire tree to test my speed and accuracy.

